{
  "texts": [
    "There are two common evaluation methods for FMs: 1) automated evaluation, and 2) human evaluation.Automated Evaluation: Automated evaluation of FMs commonly adopts standard indicators or metrics and evaluation tools to assess model performance.",
    "These include accuracy, fairness, ROUGE [225] and BERTScore [226].",
    "For instance, the BLEU score [227] has been leveraged to measure the similarity and quality between the text generated by the FM and the reference text by the machine translation task.",
    "Due to its simplicity and automatic computing, this evaluation metric is widely adopted by existing FM evaluation effort.",
    "In addition, with the deployment of FMs, more advanced automated evaluation approaches are emerging."
  ]
}